Aloe barbadensis

   [3032.jpg]
    Authority   Miller
      Family    Liliopsida:Liliidae:Asparagales:Asphodelaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3032

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herbaceous, succulent plant with rosettes of long
   pointed leaves from shortly branched creeping rhizome. The flowers are
   yellow and borne in an elogated compact raceme from the center of the
   rosette. The plant does not produce fruit. USES The sappy latex of the
   leaves has medicinal properties. The plant is grown as an ornamental.
   GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON NAMES Barbados aloe, Mediterranean
   aloe, True aloe, Aloe vera, Curacao aloe, Aloe-vera-gel. FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: A. vera, A. vulgaris, A. indica. Barbados aloe is
   probably native of subtropical South and East Africa and the
   Mediterranean region.

   Sources
   Iwu M 1993 pp 114-115 [USE, TEXT, DRA, RAIN]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 270 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 6 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]

